式为 60 毫秒。是的，如果您需要接听电话，您仍然可以通过蓝牙连接到手机。</p><p>这些与<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/razer-hammerhead-true-wireless-pro-announced-specs-pricing-availability-030051126.html">您之前看到的</a>普通 Hammerhead Pro 耳塞相似。他们仍然提供 THX 认证的声音和可定制的主动降噪 (ANC) 级别。这就是 Razer，有 Chroma RGB 灯光可以炫耀您选择的个人音频。它们的电池续航时间取决于您的连接方式和使用的设备。在禁用 ANC 和照明的情况下，您可以管理长达 6.5 小时的蓝牙收听时间，并通过支持无线充电的外壳提供 24 小时的额外电量。在启用 ANC 和照明的情况下下降到 3.5 小时，并且使用加密狗将运行时间缩短到 3 到 4 小时（加上案例中的 11 到 14.5 小时）。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Hammerhead Pro Hyperspeed 耳塞现已上市，售价 200 美元。如果您正在寻找可与您的手机和家用游戏 PC 配合使用的全能型耳塞，那么这个价格很划算。话虽如此，如果您乐于坚持使用蓝牙，有些选项可以听起来更好或持续时间更长。 Razer 的最新选择更适合那些不想<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-headset-130006477.html">单独购买游戏耳机</a>的人。 </p><p><core-commerce id="d2819c9b52054605a2c7932fd12bf789" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/razers-new-gaming-earbuds-include-a-low-latency-dongle-172423306.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/razers-new-gaming-earbuds-include-a-low-latency-dongle-172423306.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1feb1275-bc1e-45bc-81b7-1c3264b9ebeb</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 30 May 2023 17:24:23 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685467987</ingested><modified> 2023-05-30T17:33:14+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/3f315e00-ff06-11ed-b6bf-1d3148be6879" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/3f315e00-ff06-11ed-b6bf-1d3148be6879" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Razer]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Razer Hammerhead Pro HyperSpeed earbuds]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Razer Hammerhead Pro HyperSpeed earbuds]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best VPNs for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>虚拟专用网络 (VPN) 最近风头正劲。保护您的在线活动的曾经小众的方式开始流行，部分原因是大量的营销预算和有影响力的合作让消费者相信他们可以解决您所有的安全问题。但要确定最适合您浏览需求的选项，需要深入了解并不总是完全准确的属性声明。这使得更难确定订阅哪个 VPN 服务提供商，或者您是否真的需要使用一个。我们测试了目前可用的九种最佳 VPN 服务，以帮助您选择最适合您需求的一种。</p><h2>您应该了解的有关 VPN 的知识</h2><p>VPN 不是一种放之四海而皆准的安全解决方案。相反，它们只是保护您的数据隐私和安全的一部分。密歇根大学计算机科学与工程助理教授 Roya Ensafi 告诉 Engadget，VPN 无法抵御网络钓鱼攻击等常见威胁，也无法保护您的数据免遭窃取。但是，当您连接到公共某个地方的不受信任的网络时，它们确实可以派上用场以保护在线隐私，因为它们将您的流量隧道并加密到下一跳。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>换句话说，VPN 服务会掩盖您的 IP 地址和您的计算机在网络上的身份，并创建一个加密的“隧道”，以防止您的互联网服务提供商 (ISP) 访问有关您的浏览历史记录的数据。即便如此，大部分数据或信息仍由 VPN 提供商而不是您的 ISP 存储，这意味着使用设计不当或未受保护的网络仍然会破坏您的安全。</p><p>这意味着看似有希望的笼统说法，如军用级加密或完全数字隐形，可能并不完全准确。相反，消费者报告在线安全指南的项目经理 Yael Grauer 建议寻找安全功能，例如具有可复制构建的开源软件、对 WireGuard、IPsec 或 PPTP 等行业标准协议的最新支持以及能够抵御像蛮力这样的攻击向量。</p><h2> VPN 真正适合谁？</h2><p>在考虑使用 VPN 之前，请确保您的在线安全在其他方面是最新的。这意味着复杂的密码、多因素身份验证方法和锁定您的数据共享首选项。即便如此，您可能也不需要一直使用 VPN。</p><p> “If you&#39;re just worried about somebody sitting there passively and looking at your data then a VPN is great,” Jed Crandall, an associate professor at Arizona State University, told Engadget.</p><p> If you use public WiFi a lot, like while working at a coffee shop, then VPN usage can help give you private internet access. They&#39;re also helpful for hiding information from other people on your ISP if you don&#39;t want members of your household to know what you&#39;re up to online.</p><p> Geoblocking has also become a popular use case as it helps you reach services in other parts of the world. For example, you can access shows that are only available on streaming services, like Netflix, Hulu or Amazon Prime, in other countries, or play online games with people located all over the globe.</p><h2> Are VPNs worth it?</h2><p> Whether or not VPNs are worth it depends how often you could use it for the above use cases. If you travel a lot and rely on public WiFi, are looking to browse outside of your home country or want to keep your traffic hidden from your ISP, then investing in a VPN will be useful. But, keep in mind that even the best VPN services often slow down your internet speed, so they may not be ideal all the time.</p><p> We recommend not relying on a VPN connection as your main cybersecurity tool. VPN use can provide a false sense of security, leaving you vulnerable to attack. Plus, if you choose just any VPN, it may not be as secure as just relying on your ISP. That&#39;s because the VPN could be based in a country with weaker data privacy regulation, obligated to hand information over to law enforcement or linked to weak user data protection policies.</p><p> For users working in professions like activism or journalism that want to really strengthen their internet security, options like the Tor browser may be a worthwhile alternative, according to Crandall. Tor is free, and while it&#39;s less user-friendly, it&#39;s built for anonymity and privacy.</p><h2> How we tested</h2><p> To test the security specs of different VPNs and name our top picks, we relied on pre-existing academic work through <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.consumerreports.org/vpn-services/mullvad-ivpn-mozilla-vpn-top-consumer-reports-vpn-testing-a9588707317/">Consumer Reports</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://vpnalyzer.org/">VPNalyzer</a> and other sources. We referenced privacy policies, transparency reports and security audits made available to the public. We also considered past security incidents like data breaches.</p><p> We looked at price, usage limits, effects on internet speed, possible use cases, ease of use and additional “extra” features for different VPN providers. The VPNs were tested across iOS, Android and Mac devices so we could see the state of the apps across various platforms (Windows devices are also supported in most cases). We used the “quick connect” feature on the VPNs to connect to the “fastest” provider available when testing internet speed, access to IP address data and DNS and WebRTC leaks or when a fault in the encrypted tunnel reveals requests to an ISP.</p><p> Otherwise, we conducted a test of geoblocking content by accessing Canada-exclusive Netflix releases, a streaming test by watching a news livestream on YouTube via a Hong Kong-based VPN and a gaming test by playing on servers in the United Kingdom. By performing these tests at the same time, it also allowed us to test claims about simultaneous device use.</p><h3> VPNs we tested:</h3><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4255ebf1-6185-403e-9be2-91ab47ad1ac3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=ExpressVPN&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI0MjU1ZWJmMS02MTg1LTQwM2UtOWJlMi05MWFiNDdhZDFhYzMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZXhwcmVzc3Zwbi5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhZDkxNTA4Yi1iYmUxLTQ0ZTgtYTcxNi0wMjcyNGNiY2EzYWMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAfTSiO2r428NJBCpZe3eLV5R1owvIj5yByLJP3rxwv1h&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.expressvpn.com%2Foffer%2Fcoupon">ExpressVPN</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:NordVPN;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=c52a3d27-2d9a-44d8-8cf2-6f6387b122a0&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=NordVPN&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjNTJhM2QyNy0yZDlhLTQ0ZDgtOGNmMi02ZjYzODdiMTIyYTAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9ub3JkdnBuLmNvbS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImFkOTE1MDhiLWJiZTEtNDRlOC1hNzE2LTAyNzI0Y2JjYTNhYyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAQXft9OD6rLKuE3EeJnnHBCc242IE-XnNcv8hGIe48D_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F">NordVPN</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=6119f7ca-bf13-40ba-b3f6-2a335a8890f6&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=surfshark&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2MTE5ZjdjYS1iZjEzLTQwYmEtYjNmNi0yYTMzNWE4ODkwZjYiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9zdXJmc2hhcmsuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYWQ5MTUwOGItYmJlMS00NGU4LWE3MTYtMDI3MjRjYmNhM2FjIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAew67IgxBRqcZ6LIo58dh_RnSNSjrwxb8YksKDxdubiq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2Fdeals">Surfshark</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:ProtonVPN;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=06a20697-4135-4e83-a421-f326eee937ed&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=ProtonVPN&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwNmEyMDY5Ny00MTM1LTRlODMtYTQyMS1mMzI2ZWVlOTM3ZWQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wcm90b252cG4uY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYWQ5MTUwOGItYmJlMS00NGU4LWE3MTYtMDI3MjRjYmNhM2FjIn0&amp;signature=AQAAASPTOHDxtcJbE-t49l7sjJMvW4wl1inFzyOcIJYRUXYC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fprotonvpn.com%2F">Proton VPN</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:TunnelBear;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1c695770-3d23-4adf-9f4f-c595e9124f3b&amp;s